org.alljoyn.onboarding.client

Interface OnboardingClient

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.alljoyn.services.common.ClientBase
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    OnboardingClientImpl

    public interface OnboardingClient
extends org.alljoyn.services.common.ClientBase
    An interface for onboarding a remote IoE device (onboardee). Encapsulates the OnboardingTransport BusInterface

    • Method Detail

      • getState

        short getState()
               throws org.alljoyn.bus.BusException
        Returns the configured state of the onboardee
        Returns:
        the onboarding state: 0 - Personal AP Not Configured 1 - Personal AP Configured/Not Validated 2 - Personal AP Configured/Validating 3 - Personal AP Configured/Validated 4 - Personal AP Configured/Error 5 - Personal AP Configured/Retry
        Throws:
        org.alljoyn.bus.BusException

      • GetLastError

        OBLastError GetLastError()
                         throws org.alljoyn.bus.BusException
        Get the last error. During most of the onboarding process, the onboarder and onboardee are on different networks so returning a sync result isn't possible. Especially when there was an error and the onboardee did not connect to the onboarder's network. The onboardee then opens a soft AP to which the onboarder connects, and this method is how the onboarder can query about what happened.
        Returns:
        last error
        Throws:
        org.alljoyn.bus.BusException

      • configureWiFi

        OnboardingTransport.ConfigureWifiMode configureWiFi(java.lang.String ssid,
                                                  java.lang.String passphrase,
                                                  OnboardingService.AuthType authType)
                                                    throws org.alljoyn.bus.BusException
        Send the personal AP info to the onboardee. The onboardee doesn't try to connect yet. It waits for connectWiFi() When the authType is equal to "any", the onboardee needs to try out all the possible authentication types it supports to connect to the AP.
        Parameters:
        ssid - the personal AP SSID
        passphrase - the personal AP passphrase
        authType - the authentication type of the AP
        Returns:
        Wifi mode regular or fast channel
        Throws:
        org.alljoyn.bus.BusException - If authType parameter is invalid then the AllJoyn error code org.alljoyn.Error.OutOfRange will be returned

      • connectWiFi

        void connectWiFi()
                 throws org.alljoyn.bus.BusException
        Tell the onboardee to connect to the Personal AP. The onboardee is recommended to use channel switching feature if it is available. That is, keep the soft AP open with the onboarder, while trying to connect to the personal AP.
        Throws:
        org.alljoyn.bus.BusException

      • offboard

        void offboard()
              throws org.alljoyn.bus.BusException
        Tell the onboardee to disconnect from the personal AP, clear the personal AP configuration fields, and start the soft AP mode.
        Throws:
        org.alljoyn.bus.BusException

      • getScanInfo

        ScanInfo getScanInfo()
                     throws org.alljoyn.bus.BusException
        Scan all the WiFi access points in the onboardee's proximity, so that the onboarder can select the proper one. Some devices may not support this feature.
        Returns:
        ScanInfo an array of scan results.
        Throws:
        org.alljoyn.bus.BusException - If device doesn't support the feature, the AllJoyn error code org.alljoyn.Error.FeatureNotAvailable will be returned in the AllJoyn response.

      • registerConnectionResultListener

        void registerConnectionResultListener(ConnectionResultListener listener)
                                      throws org.alljoyn.bus.BusException
        Register to receive ConnectionResult signal data. This is relevant in fast channel switching mode.
        Parameters:
        listener - callback class to receive data.
        Throws:
        org.alljoyn.bus.BusException - if registration fails
